# ACT II

# SEQUENCE VII - THE RIVER BOUNDARY

FADE IN:

EXT. OKU FAMILY LAND - RIVER BOUNDARY - LATE AFTERNOON

The river moves beneath a low amber sky.

Broad. Brown. Unhurried.

Leaves and reflected light travel the current. The forest crowds both banks, older than everyone standing before it.

Bode removes his sandals and leaves them beside the exposed roots of a tree. He steps into the water until it reaches his ankles. Bends. Touches two fingers to the current.

Waits.

Then looks back at the brothers.

BODE
Face the current.

Malik removes his shoes. Ade follows.

Kai is last. Mud dries across one knee. His camera bag hangs high against his chest. Malik looks at Kai's closed, scraped hand. Kai enters the water.

Bode returns to the bank and steps back from the water.

The BRASS URN rests in Malik's hands.

Smaller now than the journey built around it.

Malik opens it. Looks down at the ash. His fingers tighten around the rim.

Ade steps beside him. Places one hand on Malik's shoulder.

Malik looks to Kai.

Kai nods.

Malik tips the urn.

The first ash touches the river and spreads in pale veils. Some sinks immediately. Some catches the current.

No music.

Water against their legs. Leaves shifting above them. Insects working invisibly in the heat.

Malik tips the urn farther. Ade lowers his head. Kai follows each grey strand until the river takes it.

A last dusting gathers along the lip.

Malik taps the base once.

One narrow ribbon of ash settles on the current.

The water moves beneath it.

The ash holds.

Kai sees it.

Then the ribbon opens. Separates. Disappears.

The river continues.

A bird calls beyond the trees.

Malik lowers the empty urn. Kneels. Rinses the ash from his fingertips.

The grey leaves his skin.

When he stands, his shoulders sit lower.

Ade looks downstream. Opens his mouth. Closes it.

Kai shuts his eyes.

The brothers remain in the current. Wind moves over the water. Sunlight breaks across it.

Then one insect stops.

A thin metallic chirr from the left bank cuts off mid-pulse.

Another disappears farther in.

Then another.

The change travels through the forest.

Life withdrawing from sound.

Ade opens his eyes.

The breeze weakens. Leaves settle. The surface of the river smooths around their legs.

A bird lands above the bank.

Does not call.

Malik's hand rises to the back of his neck.

He looks over his shoulder.

Only water. Only forest.

His body locks.

One second.

Air returns to him. He lowers his hand.

Ade turns toward the bank. The beginning of a smile finds his face.

No joke follows.

Kai remains facing downstream. His gaze fixes beyond the bend.

The trees seem closer.

He blinks.

They are where they were.

Malik stops breathing.

Ade's unfinished smile disappears.

Kai's shoulders draw tight.

All at once.

Nothing touches them.

None of them turns.

The moment passes.

Wind crosses the river. Insects restart unevenly. The bird leaves the branch. Water breaks around their ankles.

Malik steps first. Ade follows. Kai waits a beat before moving.

They leave the river separately, though they entered it together.

Bode watches from the bank.

Malik rubs the back of his neck and reaches for his collar.

Ade says nothing.

Kai keeps his eyes from the trees.

Bode looks past them toward the river.

Nothing there.

He picks up Malik's shoes and hands them over.

BODE
Let's go.

The brothers dress. Bode starts up the path faster than he walked down.

Still short of a run.

After several steps --

BODE
Don't look back.

No one does.

Behind them, the current passes over the place where the ash held together.

Nothing holds there now.

# END OF SEQUENCE VII
